76.6	Amy_Chua	Amy Chua	Amy L. Chua (simplified Chinese: ; traditional Chinese: ; pinyin: Cài Měi'ér, born October 26, 1962) is the John M. Duff, Jr. Professor of Law at Yale Law School. She joined the Yale faculty in 2001 after teaching at Duke Law School. Prior to starting her teaching career, she was a corporate law associate at Cleary, Gottlieb, Steen &amp; Hamilton. She specializes in the study of international business transactions, law and development, ethnic conflict, and globalization and the law. As of January 2011, she is most noted for her parenting memoir, Battle Hymn of the Tiger Mother.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/2f/Amychua4.png/220px-Amychua4.png
